ear petition for redres of grievance from third party unfavorable discriminate against third party refusal to allow registration a a member of a third party when register to vote in state where partisan voter registration be optional or require vote fraud stuff ballot box lose ballot fix election threaten candidate ballot print error machine vote irregularity election official refusal to register third party voter or allow file by third party candidate failure to print third party registration option on official voter registration document intimidation of third party voter candidate any other criminal act by local county state or federal election official exclusion of third party candidate from debate forum sponsor by public school state college and university and government include event carry on television and radio station own subsidize by government any other information relevant to the topic information be solicit about incident relate to all non democratic and non-republican political party such a libertarian new alliance socialist worker party natural law party taxpayer populist consumer green american communist etc a well a independent candidate such a john anderson ros perot eugene mccarthy barry commoner etc representative of the government reference above will be invite to respond to any allegation relevant section of the document of the copenhagen meeting referenced above the participate state recognize that pluralistic democracy and the rule of law be essential for ensure respect for all human right and fundamental freedom they therefore welcome the commitment express by all participate state to the ideal of democracy and political pluralism the participate state expres their conviction that full respect for human right and fundamental freedom and the development of society base on pluralistic democracy be prerequisite for progress in set up the last order of peace security justice and co-operation they therefore reaffirm their commitment to implement fully all provision of the final act and of the other csce document relate to the human dimension in order to strengthen respect for and enjoyment of human right and fundamental freedom to develop human contact and to resolve issue of a relate humanitarian character the participate state agree on the follow they consider that the rule of law do not mean merely a formal legality which assure regularity and consistency in the achievement and enforcement of democratic order but justice base on the recognition and full acceptance of the supreme value of the human personality and guarantee by institution provide a framework for it fullest expression they reaffirm that democracy be an inherent element of the rule of law they recognize the importance of pluralism with regard to political organization they confirm that they will respect each other right freely to choose and develop in accordance with international human right standard their political social economic and cultural system in exercise thi right they will ensure that their law regulation practice and policy conform with their obligation under international law and be bring into harmony with the provision of the declaration on principle and other csce commitment they solemnly declare that among those element of justice which be essential to the full expression of the inherent dignity and of the equal and inalienable right of all human be be the follow a clear separation between the state and political party in particular political party will not be merge with the state to ensure that the will of the person serve a the basi of the authority of government the participate state will ensure that vote be count and report honestly with the official result make public respect the right of citizen to seek political or public office individually or a representative of political party or organization without discrimination relevant section of the international covenant of october referenced above the state party to the present covenant recognizing that the ideal of free human be enjoy civil and political freedom and freedom from fear and want can only be achieve if condition be create whereby everyone may enjoy hi civil and political right a well a hi economic social and cultural right considering the obligation of state under the charter of the united nation to promote universal respect for and observance of human right and freedom agree upon the follow article article each state party to the present covenant undertake to respect and to ensure to all individual within it territory and subject to it jurisdiction the right recognize in the present covenant without distinction of any kind such a race colmy sex language religion political or other opinion national or social origin property birth or other statu where not already provide for by exist legislative or other measure each state party to the present covenant undertake to take the necessary step in accordance with it constitutional process and with the provision of the present covenant to adopt such legislative or other measure a may be necessary to give effect to the right recognize in the present covenant article the state party to the present covenant undertake to ensure the equal right of man and woman to the enjoyment of all civil and political right set forth in the present covenant article every citizen shall have the right and the opportunity without any of the distinction mention in article and without unreasonable restriction a to take part in the conduct of public affair directly or through freely choose representative b to vote and to be elect at genuine periodic election which shall be by universal and equal suffrage and shall be hold by secret ballot guarantee the free expression of the will of the elector c to have acces on general term of equality to public service in hi country article all person be equal before the law and be entitle without any discrimination to the equal protection of the law in thi respect the law shall prohibit any discrimination and guarantee to all person equal and effective protection against discrimination on any grind such a race colmy sex language religion political or other opinion national or social origin property birth or other statu there will be no peace without freedom think globally act locally resist much obey little question authority comment from bob waldrop be the responsibility of bob waldrop for a good time call e-mail snail mail box salt lake city utah united state of america voice phone do blame me i vote libertarian disclaimer i speak for myself except a note copyright rich thomson uucp uunet rthomson rich thomson internet rthomson irc rich pext programmer david matthew deane deane when the word fold open it mean the death of door even casement window sense the danger amon liner 